{
  "texts": [
    "Example 4.4 (Lipschitz and strongly convex loss function).",
    "Assume that Θ is convex.",
    "Assume that there are function d i: Θ 2 → R +, where each d i might depend of (X i, Y i), and assume that ℓ i satisfies:",
    "In the special case where d i (θ, θ ′) is a metric on Θ, (4.3) will be satisfied if the loss is α-strongly convex in θ, and (4.4) will be satisfied if the loss is L-Lipschitz in θ with respect to d i.",
    "For example, when using the quadratic loss"
  ]
}